---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const breadcrumbJsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://aiso-group.com/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://aiso-group.com/about/" }
  ]
};

const aboutJsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "name": "About AISO Group",
  "url": "https://aiso-group.com/about/",
  "description": "We built a group, not an agency. Four specialist AI companies, one roof, one rule: specialists beat generalists for real businesses."
};
---

<Base
  title="About — A branded house for specialist AI"
  description="We built a group, not an agency. Four specialist AI companies, one roof, one rule: specialists beat generalists for real businesses."
  jsonLd={[aboutJsonLd, breadcrumbJsonLd]}
>
  <section class="bg-[#0A1628] text-white">
    <div class="container-aiso section !py-20 md:!py-28">
      <span class="kicker kicker-on-dark mb-5 block">About AISO Group</span>
      <h1 class="h1 !text-white max-w-4xl">
        We built a branded house because generalists fail SMBs.
      </h1>
      <p class="lead !text-slate-300 mt-6">
        Four specialist AI companies under one roof. One thesis: specialists beat generalists when the work is real and the budget is finite.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container-aiso section">
      <div class="article-body">
        <h2>Why specialist AI, and why now</h2>
        <p>
          Small and mid-sized businesses do not need another generalist agency.
        </p>
        <p>
          They need a partner who knows one thing well. AI search. AI systems. Social and content. AI training. Then — when the first job is done — a partner who can hand them cleanly to the next specialist, without a re-sell.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is the group model. Not a bundle. A roster.
        </p>

        <h2>The four companies</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>AISO Hub</strong> — AI Search Optimization. The specialist practice. Calm, editorial, citation-first.</li>
          <li><strong>AISO Dev</strong> — AI Implementation for SMBs. The workshop. Technical, practical, scoped.</li>
          <li><strong>AISO Buzz</strong> — AI-Powered Social & Content. The creative studio. Brand-bible-first, results-backed.</li>
          <li><strong>AISO Learn</strong> — Corporate AI Training. The classroom. EU AI Act-aligned curricula, proof over PDFs.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Each has its own site, its own team, its own voice. All four share a design system, a footer, and a standard.
        </p>

        <h2>What we will not be</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We are not a full-service agency. If you need a bundled retainer across every marketing discipline, we are the wrong call.</li>
          <li>We are not a consultancy. We do not sell slide decks. Hub cites. Dev builds. Buzz says. Learn teaches. All four ship.</li>
          <li>We are not an AI reseller. We do not pass you to a vendor. The work is our work.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Built in Lisbon, 2025</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Founder:</strong> Greg Stoos. Lisbon-based. 16,779 LinkedIn followers. 20+ years across marketing, operations, and software.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Team:</strong> Human specialists per brand, AI-augmented throughout. Every AI output is reviewed by a human before it ships.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Legal entity:</strong> Precious Episode LDA, Lisbon, Portugal.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Focus:</strong> EU-based SMBs. English, Portuguese, French. Real businesses with real customers, not venture-backed experiments.
        </p>

        <h2>The group rules</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>One problem, one specialist.</strong> You do not need to pre-commit to a bundle. Start with the brand that fits the problem in front of you.</li>
          <li><strong>Human validation on every output.</strong> No AI content goes to a client without a human signing off.</li>
          <li><strong>Scoped engagements.</strong> Fixed timelines, fixed scopes, fixed price bands — especially at Hub and Dev. No mystery retainers.</li>
          <li><strong>Cross-referrals without re-selling.</strong> When a Hub client needs Dev, the handoff is internal. No new sales process.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>2026 is the year the generalist model breaks</h2>
        <p>
          Every SMB has the same pressure: AI changes the work faster than a generalist can keep up.
        </p>
        <p>
          A generalist shop picks one AI tool, badges it as "digital transformation," and hopes the retainer survives the quarter.
        </p>
        <p>
          A specialist shop picks the problem, ships the fix, and moves on.
        </p>
        <p>
          The cost of the wrong call — retainers spent on work that does not land — is the reason we built a group.
        </p>

        <h2>Proof</h2>
        <p>
          <em>We are new as a group. Older as operators.</em>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>AISO Hub</strong> flagship site: <a href="https://aiso-hub.com" rel="noopener">aiso-hub.com</a>. Live case studies and insights.</li>
          <li><strong>AISO Dev</strong> ships internal tooling for the AISO platform itself — the AI engine, the orchestrator, the agent-messaging system.</li>
          <li><strong>AISO Buzz</strong> runs its own social under the same methodology it sells.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Named client case studies are in review. We will publish them when the clients approve them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <a href="/#router" class="btn btn-primary">Find your AISO specialist →</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-ghost">Talk to Greg →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
